						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall, <hi rend="italic">mahā-maṇḍapa,</hi> Tiruvālanduṟaiyār temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 12: 983 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records a gift of 90 sheep by Madhurāntakan Gaṇḍarādittan for maintaining a perpetual lamp to the deity, Mahādēva, the Tiruvālanduṟai-uḍaiyār, of Śiṟupaḻuvūr, a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēya</hi> in Kuṉṟak-kūṟṟam. The donor also provided the lamp. (Cf. <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX. No. 341.)</p>						

						</summary>
